item.description:
I had to do this for a database with multiple data files. I had to change the CREATE DATABASE statement to create two data files, otherwise bring the db online would fail looking for the secondary data file. Here&#039;s the modified statement:
&lt;code lang=&quot;tsql&quot;&gt; CREATE DATABASE bah ON PRIMARY ( NAME = &#039;bah_data&#039;, FILENAME = &#039;E:\Temp\bah.mdf&#039;), ( NAME = &#039;bah_1_data&#039;, FILENAME = &#039;E:\Temp\bah_1.mdf&#039;) LOG ON ( NAME = &#039;bah_log&#039;, FILENAME = &#039;E:\Temp\bah.ldf&#039; ) GO &lt;/code&gt;
Additionally, when I brought the database online, I got this warning:
&quot;The Service Broker in database &quot;bah&quot; will be disabled because the Service Broker GUID in the database (256D7E33-1FA0-437B-B8DF-7A7AE735C3B8) does not match the one in sys.databases (116A14FA-05CC-4F3D-9C8C-94AB72CCC597).&quot;
I googled the solution to this, which is to reset the service broker (http://grumpydba.blogspot.com.au/2011/09/service-broker-guid-does-not-match-one.html):
&lt;code lang=&quot;tsql&quot;&gt; ALTER DATABASE bahSET NEW_BROKER WITH ROLLBACK IMMEDIATE GO &lt;/code&gt;

